The paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics, which are typically categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The main focus of the paper is on planar graphs, which are often studied in the context of computational geometry, falling under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The concept of queue layouts and queue number is related to data structures, which is a topic covered under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the study of graph embeddings and planarity, which are topics covered under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of the results on graph drawing, which is a topic covered under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
